Though the symptoms of mononucleosis are self-limiting, but can sometimes be severe. The symptoms can be divided into infectious, and symptoms related to hyper-reactive immune response.
The incubation period of mononucleosis is 4-7 weeks. The most common mode of transmission is through Saliva. The virus may be present in the patient's saliva with low viral load.
